<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Purchase and Sale Agreement - {{deal.name}}</title>
</head>
<body>
  {{> header documentTitle="Purchase and Sale Agreement" documentStatus=version.status documentVersion=version.version}}

  <div class="title-page">
    <h1>PURCHASE AND SALE AGREEMENT</h1>
    <div class="property-name">{{deal.name}}</div>
    <div class="property-address">
      {{deal.propertyAddress}}<br>
      {{deal.city}}, {{deal.state}} {{deal.zipCode}}
    </div>
    <div class="parties">
      <div class="party">
        <strong>SELLER:</strong><br>
        {{deal.sellerName}}
      </div>
      <div class="party">
        <strong>PURCHASER:</strong><br>
        {{deal.buyerName}}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="effective-date">
      Effective Date: ____________________
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-break"></div>

  <div class="toc">
    <h2>TABLE OF CONTENTS</h2>
    <ol class="toc-list">
      <li><a href="#article-1">Definitions</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-2">Purchase and Sale</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-3">Purchase Price and Deposits</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-4">Title and Survey</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-5">Due Diligence</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-6">Property Condition and Access</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-7">Operations Pending Closing</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-8">Representations and Warranties</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-9">Conditions to Closing</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-10">Closing</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-11">Prorations and Adjustments</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-12">Casualty and Condemnation</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-13">Default and Remedies</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-14">Brokers</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-15">Notices</a></li>
      <li><a href="#article-16">Miscellaneous</a></li>
    </ol>
    <div class="exhibits-list">
      <strong>EXHIBITS:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Exhibit A - Legal Description</li>
        <li>Exhibit B - Personal Property</li>
        <li>Exhibit C - Rent Roll</li>
        <li>Exhibit D - Service Contracts</li>
        <li>Exhibit E - Permitted Exceptions</li>
        <li>Exhibit F - Form of Deed</li>
        <li>Exhibit G - Tenant Estoppel Certificate</li>
        <li>Exhibit H - FIRPTA Affidavit</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-break"></div>

  <div class="agreement-body">
    <p class="preamble">
      THIS PURCHASE AND SALE AGREEMENT (this "<strong>Agreement</strong>") is made and entered
      into as of the Effective Date set forth above by and between <strong>{{deal.sellerName}}</strong>,
      a __________________ ("<strong>Seller</strong>"), and <strong>{{deal.buyerName}}</strong>,
      a __________________, or its permitted assigns ("<strong>Purchaser</strong>").
    </p>

    <p class="recitals-header"><strong>RECITALS:</strong></p>
    <p class="recitals">
      A. Seller is the owner of that certain real property located in {{deal.city}}, {{deal.state}},
      and more particularly described on <strong>Exhibit A</strong> attached hereto (the "<strong>Land</strong>"),
      together with all improvements located thereon (collectively, the "<strong>Property</strong>").
    </p>
    <p class="recitals">
      B. Seller desires to sell, and Purchaser desires to purchase, the Property upon the terms
      and conditions set forth herein.
    </p>
    <p class="now-therefore">
      NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants and agreements set forth herein,
      and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are
      hereby acknowledged, Seller and Purchaser agree as follows:
    </p>

    {{!-- ARTICLE 1: DEFINITIONS --}}
    <h2 id="article-1">ARTICLE 1 - DEFINITIONS</h2>
    <p>
      As used in this Agreement, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below:
    </p>
    <dl class="definitions">
      <dt>"Business Day"</dt>
      <dd>Any day other than Saturday, Sunday, or a federal holiday.</dd>

      <dt>"Closing"</dt>
      <dd>The consummation of the purchase and sale transaction contemplated by this Agreement.</dd>

      <dt>"Closing Date"</dt>
      <dd>
        The date that is {{deal.closingDays}} days after the expiration of the Due Diligence Period,
        or such earlier date as mutually agreed by the parties in writing.
      </dd>

      <dt>"Due Diligence Period"</dt>
      <dd>
        The period commencing on the Effective Date and ending at 5:00 p.m. local time on the
        date that is {{deal.dueDiligenceDays}} days thereafter.
      </dd>

      <dt>"Earnest Money"</dt>
      <dd>
        Collectively, the Initial Deposit and the Additional Deposit, together with all interest
        earned thereon.
      </dd>

      <dt>"Effective Date"</dt>
      <dd>The date on which this Agreement has been executed by both Seller and Purchaser.</dd>

      <dt>"Permitted Exceptions"</dt>
      <dd>
        Those matters set forth on <strong>Exhibit E</strong> attached hereto, together with
        any other matters approved or deemed approved by Purchaser pursuant to Article 4.
      </dd>

      <dt>"Property"</dt>
      <dd>
        Collectively, (i) the Land, (ii) all buildings, structures, fixtures, and other improvements
        located thereon, (iii) all easements, rights-of-way, and appurtenances, (iv) all personal
        property described on <strong>Exhibit B</strong>, (v) all Leases, and (vi) all Intangible Property.
      </dd>

      <dt>"Purchase Price"</dt>
      <dd>
        {{#provField "purchasePrice" model.purchasePrice}}
          {{currency model.purchasePrice}}
        {{/provField}}
        , subject to prorations and adjustments as provided herein.
      </dd>

      <dt>"Title Company"</dt>
      <dd>{{deal.titleCompanyName}}, located at {{deal.titleCompanyAddress}}.</dd>
    </dl>

    {{!-- ARTICLE 2: PURCHASE AND SALE --}}
    <h2 id="article-2">ARTICLE 2 - PURCHASE AND SALE</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>2.1 Agreement to Sell and Purchase.</strong> Subject to the terms and conditions
      of this Agreement, Seller agrees to sell to Purchaser, and Purchaser agrees to purchase
      from Seller, the Property.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>2.2 Included Property.</strong> The sale and purchase of the Property shall include:
    </p>
    <ol class="alpha-list">
      <li>
        The Land, together with all rights, privileges, easements, and appurtenances thereto;
      </li>
      <li>
        All buildings, structures, fixtures, and improvements situated on the Land;
      </li>
      <li>
        All personal property owned by Seller and used in connection with the Property,
        as described on <strong>Exhibit B</strong>;
      </li>
      <li>
        All of Seller's right, title, and interest in and to any leases, rental agreements,
        and occupancy agreements affecting the Property (the "<strong>Leases</strong>");
      </li>
      <li>
        All of Seller's right, title, and interest in and to the Service Contracts
        described on <strong>Exhibit D</strong> that Purchaser elects to assume;
      </li>
      <li>
        All of Seller's right, title, and interest in and to all warranties, guaranties,
        permits, licenses, plans, and other intangible property related to the Property
        (the "<strong>Intangible Property</strong>").
      </li>
    </ol>

    {{!-- ARTICLE 3: PURCHASE PRICE AND DEPOSITS --}}
    <h2 id="article-3">ARTICLE 3 - PURCHASE PRICE AND DEPOSITS</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>3.1 Purchase Price.</strong> The purchase price for the Property shall be
      {{#provField "purchasePrice" model.purchasePrice}}
        {{currency model.purchasePrice}}
      {{/provField}}
      (the "<strong>Purchase Price</strong>").
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>3.2 Initial Deposit.</strong> Within three (3) Business Days after the Effective
      Date, Purchaser shall deposit with the Title Company the sum of
      <strong>{{currency deal.earnestMoneyDeposit}}</strong> (the "<strong>Initial Deposit</strong>").
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>3.3 Additional Deposit.</strong> If Purchaser does not terminate this Agreement
      pursuant to Section 5.3 on or before expiration of the Due Diligence Period, Purchaser
      shall deposit with the Title Company on the first Business Day after expiration of the
      Due Diligence Period an additional sum of <strong>{{currency deal.additionalDeposit}}</strong>
      (the "<strong>Additional Deposit</strong>").
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>3.4 Payment at Closing.</strong> At Closing, Purchaser shall pay to Seller the
      balance of the Purchase Price, less the Earnest Money and subject to prorations and
      adjustments as provided herein, by wire transfer of immediately available funds.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>3.5 Independent Consideration.</strong> Notwithstanding anything to the contrary
      contained herein, the sum of One Hundred Dollars ($100.00) of the Initial Deposit (the
      "<strong>Independent Consideration</strong>") shall be non-refundable under all circumstances
      and shall be retained by Seller as consideration for Seller's execution and delivery
      of this Agreement.
    </p>

    {{!-- ARTICLE 4: TITLE AND SURVEY --}}
    <h2 id="article-4">ARTICLE 4 - TITLE AND SURVEY</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>4.1 Title Commitment.</strong> Purchaser shall obtain, at Purchaser's expense,
      a commitment for an owner's title insurance policy from the Title Company (the
      "<strong>Title Commitment</strong>").
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>4.2 Survey.</strong> Purchaser shall obtain, at Purchaser's expense, a current
      ALTA/NSPS survey of the Property (the "<strong>Survey</strong>").
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>4.3 Title Objections.</strong> On or before the expiration of the Due Diligence
      Period, Purchaser shall notify Seller in writing of any objections to the Title
      Commitment or Survey (collectively, "<strong>Title Objections</strong>"). Any matters
      not objected to shall be deemed Permitted Exceptions.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>4.4 Seller's Response.</strong> Within five (5) Business Days after receipt
      of Purchaser's Title Objections, Seller shall notify Purchaser in writing whether
      Seller elects to cure any such Title Objections. Seller shall have no obligation
      to cure any Title Objections.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>4.5 Title Policy.</strong> At Closing, the Title Company shall issue to
      Purchaser an ALTA owner's title insurance policy in the amount of the Purchase Price,
      subject only to the Permitted Exceptions.
    </p>

    {{!-- ARTICLE 5: DUE DILIGENCE --}}
    <h2 id="article-5">ARTICLE 5 - DUE DILIGENCE</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>5.1 Property Information.</strong> Within five (5) Business Days after the
      Effective Date, Seller shall deliver or make available to Purchaser copies of all
      documents and materials in Seller's possession or control relating to the Property,
      including without limitation:
    </p>
    <ol class="alpha-list">
      <li>All Leases and rent rolls;</li>
      <li>Operating statements for the prior three (3) calendar years;</li>
      <li>Property tax bills for the prior three (3) calendar years;</li>
      <li>All Service Contracts;</li>
      <li>Environmental reports;</li>
      <li>Engineering and property condition reports;</li>
      <li>As-built plans and specifications;</li>
      <li>Certificates of occupancy and permits;</li>
      <li>Insurance certificates and loss history;</li>
      <li>Utility bills for the prior twelve (12) months.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      <strong>5.2 Physical Inspections.</strong> During the Due Diligence Period, Purchaser
      and its agents shall have the right to enter the Property for purposes of conducting
      inspections, tests, and studies, subject to the following conditions:
    </p>
    <ol class="alpha-list">
      <li>Purchaser shall provide Seller with at least 24 hours' prior notice;</li>
      <li>Purchaser shall not unreasonably interfere with tenants or Seller's operations;</li>
      <li>Purchaser shall carry liability insurance acceptable to Seller;</li>
      <li>
        Purchaser shall not conduct any invasive testing without Seller's prior written consent.
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      <strong>5.3 Termination Right.</strong> If, during the Due Diligence Period, Purchaser
      determines in its sole and absolute discretion that the Property is not suitable for
      Purchaser's purposes, Purchaser may terminate this Agreement by delivering written
      notice to Seller on or before the expiration of the Due Diligence Period. Upon such
      termination, the Initial Deposit (less the Independent Consideration) shall be returned
      to Purchaser, and neither party shall have any further obligations hereunder.
    </p>

    {{!-- ARTICLE 6: PROPERTY CONDITION --}}
    <h2 id="article-6">ARTICLE 6 - PROPERTY CONDITION AND ACCESS</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>6.1 AS-IS Sale.</strong> PURCHASER ACKNOWLEDGES AND AGREES THAT, EXCEPT AS
      EXPRESSLY SET FORTH IN THIS AGREEMENT, THE PROPERTY IS BEING SOLD AND CONVEYED IN
      ITS "AS-IS, WHERE-IS" CONDITION, WITH ALL FAULTS, AND WITHOUT ANY REPRESENTATIONS
      OR WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>6.2 Purchaser's Investigation.</strong> Purchaser acknowledges that it will
      have had the opportunity to conduct a thorough investigation of the Property during
      the Due Diligence Period and will rely solely on its own investigation and not on
      any information provided by Seller.
    </p>

    {{!-- Abbreviated content for remaining articles - indicated as skeleton --}}
    <h2 id="article-7">ARTICLE 7 - OPERATIONS PENDING CLOSING</h2>
    <p>[Standard provisions regarding Seller's operation of Property pending Closing]</p>

    <h2 id="article-8">ARTICLE 8 - REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES</h2>
    <p>[Standard Seller and Purchaser representations and warranties]</p>

    <h2 id="article-9">ARTICLE 9 - CONDITIONS TO CLOSING</h2>
    <p>[Standard conditions precedent to Closing for both parties]</p>

    <h2 id="article-10">ARTICLE 10 - CLOSING</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>10.1 Time and Place.</strong> The Closing shall take place through escrow
      at the offices of the Title Company on the Closing Date, or at such other time and
      place as the parties may mutually agree.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>10.2 Seller's Deliveries.</strong> At Closing, Seller shall deliver:
    </p>
    <ol class="alpha-list">
      <li>Special Warranty Deed in the form of <strong>Exhibit F</strong>;</li>
      <li>Bill of Sale for personal property;</li>
      <li>Assignment and Assumption of Leases;</li>
      <li>Assignment and Assumption of Service Contracts;</li>
      <li>FIRPTA Affidavit;</li>
      <li>Owner's Affidavit;</li>
      <li>Keys and access devices;</li>
      <li>Such other documents as reasonably required by the Title Company.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="article-11">ARTICLE 11 - PRORATIONS AND ADJUSTMENTS</h2>
    <p>[Standard proration provisions for taxes, rents, utilities, etc.]</p>

    <h2 id="article-12">ARTICLE 12 - CASUALTY AND CONDEMNATION</h2>
    <p>[Standard casualty and condemnation provisions]</p>

    <h2 id="article-13">ARTICLE 13 - DEFAULT AND REMEDIES</h2>
    <p>[Standard default and remedies provisions including liquidated damages]</p>

    <h2 id="article-14">ARTICLE 14 - BROKERS</h2>
    <p>
      Seller and Purchaser each represent and warrant to the other that they have not
      dealt with any broker in connection with this transaction except {{deal.brokerName}},
      whose commission shall be paid by {{deal.brokerPaidBy}} pursuant to a separate agreement.
    </p>

    <h2 id="article-15">ARTICLE 15 - NOTICES</h2>
    <p>[Standard notice provisions with addresses for both parties]</p>

    <h2 id="article-16">ARTICLE 16 - MISCELLANEOUS</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>16.1 Entire Agreement.</strong> This Agreement contains the entire agreement
      between the parties and supersedes all prior agreements and understandings.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>16.2 Amendment.</strong> This Agreement may be amended only by written
      instrument signed by both parties.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>16.3 Governing Law.</strong> This Agreement shall be governed by and construed
      in accordance with the laws of the State of {{deal.state}}.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>16.4 Counterparts.</strong> This Agreement may be executed in counterparts,
      each of which shall be deemed an original.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="page-break"></div>

  {{!-- Signature Page --}}
  <div class="signature-page">
    <h3>SIGNATURE PAGE</h3>
    <p>
      IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Purchase and Sale Agreement as of
      the Effective Date.
    </p>

    <div class="signature-blocks">
      <div class="signature-block">
        <div class="signature-header">SELLER:</div>
        <div class="signature-company">{{deal.sellerName}}</div>
        <div class="signature-line"></div>
        <div class="signature-name">By: ___________________________</div>
        <div class="signature-title">Name: _________________________</div>
        <div class="signature-title">Title: _________________________</div>
        <div class="signature-title">Date: _________________________</div>
      </div>

      <div class="signature-block">
        <div class="signature-header">PURCHASER:</div>
        <div class="signature-company">{{deal.buyerName}}</div>
        <div class="signature-line"></div>
        <div class="signature-name">By: ___________________________</div>
        <div class="signature-title">Name: _________________________</div>
        <div class="signature-title">Title: _________________________</div>
        <div class="signature-title">Date: _________________________</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-break"></div>

  {{!-- Key Terms Summary --}}
  <div class="key-terms-summary">
    <h3>KEY TERMS SUMMARY</h3>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Property</strong></td>
        <td>{{deal.name}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Address</strong></td>
        <td>{{deal.propertyAddress}}, {{deal.city}}, {{deal.state}} {{deal.zipCode}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Purchase Price</strong></td>
        <td>{{currency model.purchasePrice}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Initial Deposit</strong></td>
        <td>{{currency deal.earnestMoneyDeposit}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Additional Deposit</strong></td>
        <td>{{currency deal.additionalDeposit}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Due Diligence Period</strong></td>
        <td>{{deal.dueDiligenceDays}} days</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Closing</strong></td>
        <td>{{deal.closingDays}} days after DD expiration</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Title Company</strong></td>
        <td>{{deal.titleCompanyName}}</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    {{> provenance-table fields=provenanceFields inputs=inputs}}
  </div>

  {{> footer documentTitle="Purchase and Sale Agreement" documentVersion=version.version}}
</body>
</html>

